== RUST BACKEND API CONTRACT ==

### API Types (crates/api-types/src/)
- All IDs are UUID strings
- SessionStatus: Pending, Running, Completed, Failed
- WorkflowType: Chat, LoopN, LoopUntilSentinel, Inbox
- SessionParams: prompt, n, sentinel, agent_cli, model, branch_mode, branch_name_prefix
- CreateSessionRequest: repo_url, ref?, workflow, params?, persona_id?, identity_id?, retain_forever?
- SessionSummary: session_id, repo_url, workflow, status, created_at, updated_at?, retain_forever?
- SessionDetail: extends SessionSummary + params, persona_id, identity_id, jobs[]
- JobSummary: job_id, status, created_at, error_message?, pull_request_url?, branch?, commit_ref? (added in this task)
- SendInputRequest: message
- TaskCompleteRequest: status, worker_id, branch?, commit_ref?, mr_title?, mr_description?, error_message?, output?, sentinel_reached?, assistant_reply?

### Session Routes (crates/server/src/routes/sessions.rs)
- POST /sessions - Create session
- GET /sessions - List sessions (?status=&cursor=&limit=50)
- GET /sessions/:id - Get session detail with jobs
- PATCH /sessions/:id - Update (retain_forever)
- DELETE /sessions/:id - Delete session cascade
- POST /sessions/:id/input - Send chat follow-up
- GET /sessions/:id/events - SSE session events

### Identity Routes
- GET /identities/:id - Identity status (token presence)
- GET /identities/:id/auth-status - Token health
- GET /identities/:id/repositories?provider= - List repos
- PATCH /identities/:id - Update identity tokens

### Log Routes
- GET /sessions/:id/logs - Get session logs paginated
- GET /sessions/:id/logs/stream - SSE log stream
- DELETE /sessions/:id/logs - Delete logs

### Database Schema (jobs table)
```sql
CREATE TABLE jobs (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    session_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES sessions(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    worker_id TEXT REFERENCES workers(id),
    status TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending',
    task_input JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',
    error_message TEXT,
    branch TEXT,
    commit_ref TEXT,
    mr_title TEXT,
    mr_description TEXT,
    pull_request_url TEXT,
    output TEXT,
    sentinel_reached BOOLEAN DEFAULT false,
    assistant_reply TEXT,
    ...
);
```

